Minimal code examples (Kotlin, using KTX)

Log an Analytics event

```kotlin
val firebaseAnalytics = Firebase.analytics
val bundle = Bundle().apply {
    putString("item_name", "cool_hat")
    putDouble("price", 29.99)
}
firebaseAnalytics.logEvent("purchase", bundle)
```

Write to Firestore

```kotlin
val db = Firebase.firestore
val user = hashMapOf(
    "name" to "Ada Lovelace",
    "email" to "ada@example.com"
)
db.collection("users")
    .add(user)
    .addOnSuccessListener { docRef -> Log.d(TAG, "Added with ID: ${docRef.id}") }
    .addOnFailureListener { e -> Log.w(TAG, "Error adding document", e) }
```

Check current Auth user

```kotlin
val user = Firebase.auth.currentUser
if (user != null) {
    // User is signed in
    textView.text = "Hello, ${user.displayName}"
}
```

