```

Useful for:

· Deploying security rules, hosting, Cloud Functions.
· Managing Firestore indexes.
· Listing/exporting data (e.g., firebase firestore:export).
· CI/CD integration.

3. Firebase Management API (REST)

For fully programmatic control – create projects, add apps, manage SHA-256 fingerprints, etc. Accessible via:

· Client libraries (Node.js, Python, Go, etc.)
· The gcloud CLI (Google Cloud side): gcloud projects, gcloud firebase

Example: list Firebase projects

```bash
gcloud firebase projects list
```

4. Google Cloud Console (advanced)

Since Firebase projects are Google Cloud projects, many deeper settings live here:

· Billing, IAM, service accounts, Cloud Storage buckets, Cloud Logging.
· Firebase Management API relies on Cloud IAM.

