3. Cloud Functions for backend logic

Use case: Anything you don’t trust the client to do: data validation, payments, heavy calculations, integrating third-party APIs.

Basic structure (TypeScript)

```typescript
import * as functions from "firebase-functions";
import * as admin from "firebase-admin";
admin.initializeApp();

export const createProfile = functions.auth.user().onCreate((user) => {
  return admin.firestore().collection("users").doc(user.uid).set({
    email: user.email,
    createdAt: admin.firestore.FieldValue.serverTimestamp(),
  });
});

export const aggregateReview = functions.firestore
  .document("reviews/{reviewId}")
  .onCreate(async (snap, context) => {
    // update product average rating
  });
```

· Deploy with firebase deploy --only functions.
· In Android, you can call Callable Functions directly from the SDK:
  ```kotlin
  val addMessage = Firebase.functions.getHttpsCallable("addMessage")
  addMessage.call(data).continueWith { ... }
  ```

Performance tip

Minimize cold starts; keep functions warm if latency is critical.

