7. CI/CD & deployment

Automate everything so you never manually deploy rules or functions again.

Typical workflow (GitHub Actions example)

```yaml
steps:
  - uses: actions/checkout@v3
  - uses: actions/setup-node@v3
  - run: npm install -g firebase-tools
  - name: Deploy Firestore rules and indexes
    run: firebase deploy --only firestore:rules,firestore:indexes --token "${{ secrets.FIREBASE_TOKEN }}"
  - name: Deploy Cloud Functions
    run: firebase deploy --only functions --token "${{ secrets.FIREBASE_TOKEN }}"
```

For Android app builds, combine with Gradle build, signing, and Google Play upload.

Pro tips

· Use Firebase App Distribution (now part of Firebase) in CI to distribute builds to testers.
· Always lint and test security rules with firebase emulators:exec.
· Separate environments (dev, prod) using different Firebase projects. Switch google-services.json per build type.

